# Baseline Results Directory

This directory stores baseline performance test results for comparison.

## Creating Baselines

Run the baseline script to create a new baseline:

```bash
npm run load-test:baseline
```

This will:
1. Run the load test
2. Save results to `load-tests/results/comprehensive-load-latest.json`
3. Copy results to `load-tests/baselines/load-baseline.json`

## Baseline Files

- `load-baseline.json` - Load test baseline
- `stress-baseline.json` - Stress test baseline (optional)
- `soak-baseline.json` - Soak test baseline (optional)

## When to Update Baselines

Update baselines when:
- Infrastructure changes (new servers, database upgrades)
- Major performance optimizations are implemented
- API changes that affect performance
- After validating that new performance is acceptable

## Baseline Format

Baselines are k6 JSON output files containing:
- HTTP request metrics (duration, failure rate)
- Custom metrics (auth duration, upload duration, etc.)
- Test metadata (duration, VUs, etc.)
